This platform measures 1.44 m north south-by-2.48 m east west. The only ashlar in the north measures 0.33 m-to-0.35 m in width. A row of headers, averaging 0.73 m in length-by-0.34 m in width. The southernmost row is comprised of three headers that have been plastered over. In toto this row measures 2.00 m in east west width-by-0.30 m in north south length. Between the rows is an earth fill approximately 0.13 m in width.
Locus 13 the entry level threshold and Locus 11, the lower stairs as well as Locus 6 the northwest wall and Locus 7 the northeast wall.
With all the construction wall loci of this Trench 88. Loci 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7, 9, 10, 11, and 13.

This platform is composed of white sandstone or limestone flooring slabs that are set on a slight angle in that they are not perpendicular to the Locus 11 lower steps. It appears as if this landing platform was modified in antiquity perhaps when the sidewalk for the Colonnaded Street was constructed. The depth of the pavers averages 0.07 m
